claim.claim-text:
1. A connector comprising:
a contact having a contacting portion;
an insulating housing holding the contact; and
a conductive shell coupled with the housing;
the housing having an inner surface defining a coupling hole adapted to receive a mating connector in a first direction, the coupling hole opening at a front coupling surface of the housing having a recess;
the contacting portion being disposed in the coupling hole;
the conductive shell comprising:
a main body covering the front coupling surface and having an opening edge defining an insertion opening interfacing with the coupling hole;
a guide portion having fixing members at one end and extending along the inner surface of the housing to guide movement of the mating connector in the first direction; and
a projecting portion connected between the main body and the guide portion to protrude though the recess and outwardly from the main body and insulating housing in a direction perpendicular to the first direction, the projecting portion being of a U-shape in section and positioning the shell relative to the housing.
